        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 6:32PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 632 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Lowndesboro to 8 miles east of Camden. Movement
was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayneville, Hyundai Motors Of Alabama, Beechwood, Carters Hill,
Dublin, Carlowville, Minter, Snowdoun, Clover Hill, Grady, Sellers,
Davenport, Ramer, Cecil, Pintlala, Farmersville, Lowndes County
Airport, Calhoun, Mosses, and Strata.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
south central and southeastern Alabama.</instruction>
